<h2>What is this?</h2>

<p>This screen shows you the details of an assignment you selected in
the previous screen.  It shows what group the assignment is associated
with, what the title of the assignment is, when the assignment is
(was) due (Year-Month-Day), a description of or instructions for the
assignment.  In addition, it shows documents assignments, rubrics, and evaluation vectors associated with that assignment.</p>

<h2>How do I use it?</h2>
<p>A student can use this information to learn what needs to be done for an assignment and the criteria by which the assignment will be judged.  If you don't understand what an evaluation vector is from the title, click on it to find out exactly what it is.</p>
<p>If you want to view an actual file uploaded to the assignment, click on the link in the Native File column.  If you want to annotate a file uploaded to the assignment, click on the link in the Webified File column.  If you want to see a plain text file that the system generated from the document uploaded to the system, click on the Text File column.</p>
<p>If you want to upload, or save, a document to this assignment, click on the &quot;hand in a document&quot; link.</p>
[% IF User.isTeacher %]
<p>If you select the &quot;Evaluate&quot; link, you will be able to evaluate the document according to the evaluation vectors associated with the assignment (both independent evaluation vectors and those associated with the assignment through a rubric).</p>

<p>  The File Stats column is used to see the surface statistics associated with the document.  The &quot;view average stats&quot; link at the bottom is an average of all the surface statistics generated for each file associated with the assignment.</p>
[% END %]